    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[Complete the following proof.
<center>
<div class="proof">
<p>Let \(P(n)\) be the statement<p>
<p>{@p0@}</p>
<div class="proof-block">
<p>Since \( {@ev(ak,k=1)@} =\) [[validation:ans1]] [[input:ans1]]</p>
<p>and \( {@ev(rh0,n=1)@} = \)  [[validation:ans2]] [[input:ans2]]</p>
<p>it follows that \(P(1)\) is true.</p>
[[feedback:prtbase]]
</div>
<div class="proof-block">
<p>Assume that \(P(n)\) is true. </p>
<p>\({@lh1@} = \)  [[validation:ans3]] [[input:ans3]] </p>
<p>\( = {@rh0@} + {@ev(ak,k=n+1)@}\) [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]]</p>
<p>\( = {@factor(rh0+ev(ak,k=n+1))@}\) </p>
<p>\( = \) [[validation:ans5]] [[input:ans5]]  </p>
[[feedback:prtind]]
</div>
<p>Since \(P(1)\) and \(P(n)\Rightarrow P(n+1)\) it follows that \(P(n)\) is true for all \(n\in\mathbb{N}\) by the principal of mathematical induction.</p>
</div>
</center>
<br />]]></text>
